---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../../components/SectionHeader.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Architecture | ForgeCore" description="The control layer, workers, assets, channels, monetization, and telemetry that define ForgeCore.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="reading">
      <SectionHeader eyebrow="Architecture" title="Architecture is the control layer." description="ForgeCore treats models as interchangeable workers inside a larger operating system." />
      <div class="prose">
        <h3>Control layer</h3>
        <p>Defines objectives, constraints, scoring rules, priorities, and the criteria for allocation.</p>
        <h3>Workers and models</h3>
        <p>Language models and automations perform bounded tasks. They are labor, not strategy.</p>
        <h3>Asset layer</h3>
        <p>The system produces pages, research, issues, reports, code, and monetizable digital objects.</p>
        <h3>Channel layer</h3>
        <p>Assets are distributed through search, newsletters, social, direct outreach, partnerships, or paid acquisition if justified.</p>
        <h3>Monetization layer</h3>
        <p>Revenue paths are modular: products, affiliates, ads, subscriptions, tools, lead generation, or other comparable structures.</p>
        <h3>Telemetry layer</h3>
        <p>Measurement decides what survives. The system learns from outcomes, not wishful thinking.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
